<seg id=1> Series Of Mishaps With South Korean Military, Opposition Party Calls For Defense Minister's Resignation </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (REUTERS WIRE Seoul) The opposition party in South Korea demanded the resignation of Defense Minister Cho Seong-tae yesterday. The military has had a few accidents recently, including guided missiles and flare grenades being launched into civilian districts. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> A South Korean official said that the latest accident occurred yesterday. Some exercises at dawn went wrong, and a casing from a flare grenade went through two walls of an elderly woman's home. </seg>
<seg id=4> She lives near where shards from a guided missile explosion landed two days ago. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> A military official said that when the marine corps launched the flare grenades they went farther than anticipated, landing on the house in Kimpo. </seg>
<seg id=6> Kimpo is west of Seoul. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The opposition Grand National Party released a statement saying, "Cho Seong-Tae must either resign immediately or (President Kim Dae-jung) must discharge him from his position. </seg>
<seg id=8> A government that does not fear the people is not a government of the people." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The statement said, "Cho Seong-tae has tried to keep his post, he has only expressed an apology ... this is the height of arrogance." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> The defense ministry issued an apology for the guided missile accident that happened the day before yesterday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> A navy official said the casing from the flare grenade went through two walls and entered a bathroom. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> He said that the 83 year-old woman went into shock and was treated at a nearby hospital. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> Last Friday the military accidentally launched a surface-to-air guided missile which exploded in the air, injuring at least three civilians. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> A defense ministry official said that technicians at the airbase at the western port city of Inchon were inspecting the equipment when the missile was accidentally fired. </seg>
<seg id=15> Inchon is 40 kilometers from the border with North Korea. </seg>
</p>
